  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "This morning Chef wants to jump a little. In a few minutes he will arrive at the point **0**. Then he will perform a lot of jumps in such a sequence: **1**-jump, **2**-jump, **3**-jump, **1**-jump, **2**-jump, **3**-jump, **1**-jump, and so on.\n\n**1**-jump means that if Chef is at the point **x**, he will jump to the point **x+1**. \n\n**2**-jump means that if Chef is at the point **x**, he will jump to the point **x+2**. \n\n**3**-jump means that if Chef is at the point **x**, he will jump to the point **x+3**. \n\nBefore the start Chef asks you: will he arrive at the point **a** after some number of jumps?",
    "constraints": [
      "**0** ≤ **a** ≤ **1018**"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "The first line contains a single integer **a** denoting the point Chef asks about.",
    "outputFormat": "Output \"yes\" without a quotes if Chef can arrive at point **a** or \"no\" without a quotes otherwise.",
